{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KwFT4Sc7nGCJHN8daCVFj9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 9)\n2\t\n3\t### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — create-story (2026-04-03T09:20)\n4\t\n5\t- **Ambiguity: OpenCode CLI output format.** Architecture doc acknowledges must be \"reverse-engineered from real CLI output.\" Fixtures will be plausible guesses.\n6\t- **Ambiguity: OpenCode auth check command.** Used `opencode auth status` as guess. Low risk — health check gracefully handles command failure.\n7\t- **No project-context.md found** — workflow references it but none exists. No impact.\n8\t- **Risk: classifyError duplication.** Both CodexDriver and OpenCodeDriver have identical implementations. Intentional per architecture.\n9\t\n10\tToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 7, Grep: 4, Glob: 2, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 10 unique files read. No redundancy.\n11\t\n12\t### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — dev-story (2026-04-03T09:25)\n13\t\n14\tNo issues reported. Build passes, 4478 tests pass across 166 test files, zero regressions.\n15\t\n16\tToken Report: 20 tool calls (Bash: 4, Read: 11, Edit: 3, Write: 6, Glob: 2, Skill: 1). 11 unique files, 12 total reads. No redundancy.\n17\t\n18\t### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — code-review (2026-04-03T09:30)\n19\t\n20\t- **LOW: Dead fixture files.** test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/*.txt exist but tests use inline data. Dead artifacts.\n21\t- **LOW: classifyError/parseLine duplication.** ~80 identical lines between codex.ts and opencode.ts. Intentional per architecture.\n22\t- **LOW: console.debug for unparseable lines.** No structured logger. Shared pattern across drivers.\n23\t- No HIGH or MEDIUM issues. 96.78% coverage. All 169 files above 80% floor.\n24\t\n25\tToken Report: 12 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 7, Edit: 1, Grep: 1, Glob: 3, Skill: 1). 8 unique files. No redundancy.\n26\t\n27\t### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — verif