anning-artifacts/prd-validation-report.md-95-\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-validation-report.md-96-### Traceability Validation\n--\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-validation-report.md-237-3. FR36: specify cost routing hint mechanism (TUI advisory when >2x cheapest alternative)\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-validation-report.md-238-4. FR37: specify \"queryable format\" concretely (JSON via CLI command)\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-validation-report.md:239:5. NFR12/NFR18: add explicit \"as measured by\" clauses\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-validation-report.md-240-\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-validation-report.md-241-**This PRD is ready for architecture and epic breakdown.**\n--\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-102-4. Session boundary management (fresh/continue per task)\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-103-5. Blind evaluator agent — subjective verification, no source access, Docker + observability, structured JSON verdict\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md:104:6. Evaluator finding injection into retry prompts\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-105-7. Score-based circuit breaker (replaces file-change counting)\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-106-8. Trace ID generation and injection per iteration\n--\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-353-- FR16: System reads resolved workflow and sprint-status.yaml to drive execution\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-354-- FR17: System executes `per-story` tasks once for each story in the sprint\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md:355:- FR18: System executes `per-run` tasks once after all stories in the current phase complete\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-356-- FR19: System dispatches agents via programmatic API with compiled subagent definitions\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-357-- FR20: System spawns fresh sessions or continues existing ones based on task session boundary config\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-358-- FR21: System passes defined input contracts to each task and collects defined outputs\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md:359:- FR22: System generates a unique trace ID per iteration and injects it into agent prompts\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-360-- FR23: System enforces `source_access: false` by spawning the agent in a workspace with no source code\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-361-\n--\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-370-### Feedback Loop\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-371-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md:372:- FR29: System injects evaluator findings (specific per-AC failure details with evidence) into the retry task's agent prompt\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-373-- FR30: System filters retry execution to only the stories the evaluator flagged as failed\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-374-- FR31: System executes flow loop steps until all ACs pass or circuit breaker triggers\n--\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-383-### Observability\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-384-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md:385:- FR36: System generates and injects trace IDs that correlate across iteration → agent prompt → logs → metrics → traces\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-386-- FR37: Evaluator can query observability endpoints (VictoriaLogs, VictoriaMetrics, VictoriaTraces) during verification\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-387-\n--\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-437-- NFR16: Zero shell scripts in the execution path — all orchestration logic in compiled application code\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-438-- NFR17: Net negative LOC change after legacy removal\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md:439:- NFR18: All public functions have explicit TypeScript types (no `any` in API surface)\n--\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-overhaul.md-466-- **FR16:** Verifier can use agent-browser to navigate web UIs, interact with elements, and capture annotated screenshots as evidence\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-overhaul.md-467-- **FR17:** System can detect `[FAIL]` verdicts in proof documents (outside code blocks) and reject the proof\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-overhaul.md:468:- **FR18:** System can detect `[ESCALATE]` verdicts and count them separately from failures\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-overhaul.md-469-- **FR19:** Verification adapts approach based on project type — never refuses verification for any project category\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-overhaul.md-470-- **FR20:** Verifier session has `--allowedTools` configured so it doesn't hang on permission prompts\n--\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-overhaul.md-538-### Maintainability\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-overhaul.md-539-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-overhaul.md:540:- **NFR18:** No source file shall exceed 300 lines. Current init.ts (719 lines) must be split.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-overhaul.md-541-- **NFR19:** Module interfaces shall be documented with TypeScript types — no `any`.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-overhaul.md-542-- **NFR20:** Patches shall be markdown files readable by both humans and agents, not embedded code strings.\n--\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-26-codeharness is an npm CLI and Claude Code plugin that orchestrates autonomous coding agents across multiple frameworks — Claude Code, OpenAI Codex, OpenCode (with omo), and gstack — through a single workflow engine. Today, each coding agent framework is a silo: you pick one and live with its strengths and blind spots. codeharness breaks that lock-in by letting you define workflows where each task dispatches to the best framework and model for the job.\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-27-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:28:The critical use case is **cross-framework verification**: develop a feature in Claude Code with Opus, then verify it in Codex with a completely independent agent runtime. The verifier literally cannot cheat — it's a different binary, different model, different context. This architectural separation of concerns delivers trust that same-framework self-verification cannot.\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-29-\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-30-The workflow engine already exists (`tasks → flow` YAML with loop blocks). This PRD extends it with per-task `driver` and `model` fields, a driver abstraction that wraps each framework's CLI, and a live TUI workflow visualization showing the current position in the execution graph.\n--\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-34-### What Makes This Special\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-35-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:36:- **Cross-framework verification by architecture** — dev and verify tasks run on different agent runtimes. Independence is structural, not policy. The verifier has no access to the developer's context, tools, or session.\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-37-- **Mix-and-match orchestration** — each workflow task specifies its own driver (claude-code, codex, opencode) and model. Use Opus for complex architecture, Sonnet for routine implementation, Codex for cost-effective batch verification.\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-38-- **Plugin ecosystem integration** — gstack skills run inside Claude Code sessions, omo agents run inside OpenCode sessions. codeharness orchestrates at the framework level; plugins orchestrate within each framework.\n--\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-137-| Codex CLI output format undocumented or changes | Driver breaks | Integration tests with real CLI output snapshots, pin codex version |\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-138-| OpenCode CLI output format differs from expected | Driver parsing fails | Start with simplest output mode, iterate on real output |\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:139:| Cross-framework context passing loses information | Verification gets incomplete picture | Output contracts are explicit JSON — test with round-trip validation |\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-140-| Driver spawn latency too high | UX degradation | Profile first, optimize later. 3s target is generous for CLI cold start |\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-141-| Codex/OpenCode CLI auth model incompatible with headless use | Can't run in autonomous loop | Test headless auth early. Fall back to whichever driver works first |\n--\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-293-### Innovation Risk Mitigation\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-294-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:295:See **Project Scoping & Phased Development → Risk Mitigation Strategy** for full risk analysis. Key innovation-specific risks: CLI output format instability (mitigated by pinned versions + integration tests), cross-framework context loss (mitigated by explicit output contracts), and framework permission model differences (mitigated by driver capability matrix).\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-296-\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-297-## Developer Tool Specific Requirements\n--\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-391-- FR16: System can execute a workflow where consecutive tasks use different drivers (e.g., implement on claude-code, verify on codex)\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-392-- FR17: System can serialize a task's output contract to a structured JSON file after task completion\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:393:- FR18: System can load a previous task's output contract and inject it as context into the next task's prompt\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-394-- FR19: System can pass acceptance criteria, changed file lists, and test results across framework boundaries via output contracts\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-395-- FR20: System can execute verification tasks on a different framework than implementation tasks within the same story\n--\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-462-- NFR16: Driver timeout must be configurable per task (default: 30 minutes). Exceeded timeout terminates the driver process cleanly.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md-463-- NFR17: TUI must remain responsive during driver failures — a crashed driver must not freeze the render loop\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:464:- NFR18: Workflow engine must be idempotent for re-runs — restarting a failed workflow resumes from the last completed task, not from scratch"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NxoLQrDSbN8zX2VNmPKjEA","session_id":"8f19e005-5742-4a5a-a61f-d8a88dc16bec","uuid":"db108083-ac99-4b95-a17a-f980594276be","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:25:19.697Z"}
