{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01C5MehsTfY23j2CBRX28n4h","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** 13-2-output-contract-prompt-injection\n**Issues Found:** 3 High/Medium, 3 Low\n\n**Fixed (HIGH/MEDIUM):**\n\n1. **MEDIUM — `dispatchTask()` public API missing `previousOutputContract` parameter.** The internal `dispatchTaskWithResult()` accepted the parameter, but the public `dispatchTask()` didn't forward it, making the wiring dead code for story 13-3. Fixed by adding optional `previousOutputContract` parameter to `dispatchTask()`.\n\n2. **MEDIUM — No workflow engine integration test for contract injection (AC #10).** Zero tests proved the workflow engine actually called `buildPromptWithContractContext` or that a contract flowed through to the driver. Fixed by adding a `vi.mock` for `output-contract.js`, and 2 integration tests: one verifying contract passthrough, one verifying null default.\n\n3. **MEDIUM — Missing boundary test for output truncation at exactly 2001 characters.** Tests only covered 2000 (no truncation) and 3000 (truncation), not the exact boundary. Fixed by adding a test for 2001 chars.\n\n**Not Fixed (LOW):**\n\n4. **LOW — No markdown sanitization in `formatContractAsPromptContext`.** Contract fields like `taskName` could contain markdown that gets injected raw. By design per story notes (\"Do NOT validate the contract schema at injection time\").\n\n5. **LOW — Cost formatting uses `toFixed(2)` which may show `$0.00` for very small costs.** Sub-cent costs round to zero. Cosmetic only.\n\n6. **LOW — No test for concurrent contract writes to the same directory.** Existing atomic write pattern (write-then-rename) handles this, but no concurrent test exists.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- MEDIUM: `dispatchTask()` public API didn't expose `previousOutputContract`, making the workflow engine integration incomplete for story 13-3\n- MEDIUM: No integration test proving contract injection actually flows through the workflow engine to drivers\n- MEDIUM: Missing 2001-char boundary test for truncation\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- No markdown sanitization in prompt context formatting (by design per story notes)\n- `toFixed(2)` cost formatting shows `$0.00` for sub-cent costs\n- No concurrent write test for output contracts\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Overall: 96.8% (passes 90% target)\n- All 170 files above 80% per-file floor\n- No integration test for `dispatchTaskWithResult` called directly from loop block execution (lines 612, 627) with a contract — those code paths still don't pass contracts\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The `previousOutputContract` parameter is positional (8th parameter on `dispatchTask`). Story 13-3 should consider refactoring to an options object if the parameter list grows further.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:** None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 25\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 10, Edit: 6, Grep: 5, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit` (~30 lines), `git diff HEAD` (~200 lines), `npx vitest run workflow-engine` (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 12 total reads (workflow-engine.test.ts read 3 times at different offsets)\n- Redundant operations: none significant — workflow-engine.test.ts was read at 3 different offsets to understand the mock structure, test patterns, and find the insertion point"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a21da6a14de0623b5 (use SendMessage with to: 'a21da6a14de0623b5' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 65892\ntool_uses: 55\nduration_ms: 315993</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f19e005-5742-4a5a-a61f-d8a88dc16bec","uuid":"c7be1417-9acb-4201-a200-f52ab3279332","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:36:53.668Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-2-output-contract-prompt-injection.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls","agentId":"a21da6a14de0623b5","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** 13-2-output-contract-prompt-injection\n**Issues Found:** 3 High/Medium, 3 Low\n\n**Fixed (HIGH/MEDIUM):**\n\n1. **MEDIUM — `dispatchTask()` public API missing `previousOutputContract` parameter.** The internal `dispatchTaskWithResult()` accepted the parameter, but the public `dispatchTask()` didn't forward it, making the wiring dead code for story 13-3. Fixed by adding optional `previousOutputContract` parameter to `dispatchTask()