{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016s85SE3KG3mXxpQNsLkRQN","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 13.2: Output Contract Prompt Injection\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want the previous task's output contract injected into the next task's prompt,\n11\tso that cross-framework tasks have context from the previous step.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a new `formatContractAsPromptContext(contract: OutputContract): string` function in `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts`\n16\t   **When** called with a valid `OutputContract`\n17\t   **Then** it returns a structured text block containing: changed files list, test results summary, output summary, and AC statuses\n18\t   **And** the formatted string is human-readable and parseable by any LLM\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** a contract with `changedFiles: [\"src/api/users.ts\", \"src/api/users.test.ts\"]`\n22\t   **When** `formatContractAsPromptContext()` formats it\n23\t   **Then** the output contains a \"Changed Files\" section listing each file\n24\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n25\t\n26\t3. **Given** a contract with `testResults: { passed: 12, failed: 0, coverage: 98.5 }`\n27\t   **When** `formatContractAsPromptContext()` formats it\n28\t   **Then** the output contains a \"Test Results\" section with passed, failed, and coverage values\n29\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t4. **Given** a contract with `testResults: null`\n32\t   **When** `formatContractAsPromptContext()` formats it\n33\t   **Then** the \"Test Results\" section shows \"No test results available\" (not an error, not omitted)\n34\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n35\t\n36\t5. **Given** a contract with `acceptanceCriteria: [{ id: \"AC1\", description: \"User can register\", status: \"implemented\" }]`\n37\t   **When** `formatContractAsPromptContext()` formats it\n38\t   **Then** the output contains an \"Acceptance Criteria\" section listing each AC with its id, description, and status\n39\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n40\t\n41\t6. **Given** a contract with an empty `changedFiles` array and `null` testResults\n42\t   **When** `formatContractAsPromptContext()` formats it\n43\t   **Then** it still returns a valid string (no crashes on empty/null fields)\n44\t   **And** sections for empty data indicate \"none\" or similar, not blank\n45\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n46\t\n47\t7. **Given** `formatContractAsPromptContext()` returns a formatted string\n48\t   **When** the string is examined\n49\t   **Then** it includes the task name, driver, model, cost, and duration from the contract as a context header\n50\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n51\t\n52\t8. **Given** a new `buildPromptWithContractContext(basePrompt: string, previousContract: OutputContract | null): string` function in `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts`\n53\t   **When** called with a non-null `previousContract`\n54\t   **Then** it returns `basePrompt` followed by a separator and the formatted contract context\n55\t   **And** the separator clearly delineates the original prompt from the injected context\n56\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n57\t\n58\t9. **Given** `buildPromptWithContractContext()` is called with `previousContract: null`\n59\t   **When** no previous contract exists (first task in workflow)\n60\t   **Then** it returns the `basePrompt` unchanged (no injection, no separator)\n61\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n62\t\n63\t10. **Given** the workflow engine in `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` dispatches a task\n64\t    **When** `DispatchOpts` is constructed and the task has a non-null `outputContract` field\n65\t    **Then** the engine uses `buildPromptWithContractContext()` to prepend/append contract context to the prompt\n66\t    **And** the injection works regardless of which driver is used (claude-code, codex, opencode)\n67\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n68\t\n69\t11. **Given** the `formatContractAsPromptContext()` output\n70\t    **When** the output is measured\n71\t    **Then** the `output` field from the contract is truncated to at most 2000 characters to avoid prompt bloat\n72\t    **And** truncation is indicated with a `[truncated]` marker\n73\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n74\t\n75\t12. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n76\t    **When** the build completes\n77\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n78\t    **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n79\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n80\t\n81\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n82\t\n83\t- [x] Task 1: Implement `formatContractAsPromptContext()` in `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5, #6, #7, #11)\n84\t  - [x] Add function signature: `export function formatContractAsPromptContext(contract: OutputContract): string`\n85\t  - [x] Format header section: task name, driver, model, cost, duration, timestamp\n86\t  - [x] Format \"Changed Files\" section: list files or \"None\"\n87\t  - [x] Format \"Test Results\" section: passed/failed/coverage or \"No test results available\"\n88\t  - [x] Format \"Output Summary\" section: truncate `contract.output` to 2000 chars with `[truncated]` marker\n89\t  - [x] Format \"Acceptance Criteria\" section: list each AC with id, description, status\n90\t  - [x] Return the assembled string\n91\t\n92\t- [x] Task 2: Implement `buildPromptWithContractContext()` in `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` (AC: #8, #9)\n93\t  - [x] Add function signature: `export function buildPromptWithContractContext(basePrompt: string, previousContract: OutputContract | null): string`\n94\t  - [x] If `previousContract` is `null`, return `basePrompt` unchanged\n95\t  - [x] Otherwise, call `formatContractAsPromptContext(previousContract)` and append to `basePrompt` with a clear separator (e.g., `\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Previous Task Context\\n\\n`)\n96\t\n97\t- [x] Task 3: Wire injection into workflow engine (AC: #10)\n98\t  - [x] In `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`, in the `dispatchTaskWithResult()` function\n99\t  - [x] Before constructing `DispatchOpts`, check if `opts.outputContract` (or a passed-in previous contract) exists\n100\t  - [x] Use `buildPromptWithContractContext(prompt, previousContract)` to build the final prompt\n101\t  - [x] Pass the enriched prompt in `DispatchOpts.prompt` — this is framework-agnostic since all drivers consume the prompt field\n102\t\n103\t- [x] Task 4: Update barrel exports in `src/lib/agents/index.ts` (AC: #1)\n104\t  - [x] Add `formatContractAsPromptContext` and `buildPromptWithContractContext` to exports\n105\t\n106\t- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#12)\n107\t  - [x] Create or extend `src/lib/agents/__tests__/output-contract.test.ts`\n108\t  - [x] Test: `formatContractAsPromptContext` produces sections for changed files, test results, AC statuses, output summary, header\n109\t  - [x] Test: `formatContractAsPromptContext` handles `null` testResults gracefully\n110\t  - [x] Test: `formatContractAsPromptContext` handles empty changedFiles array\n111\t  - [x] Test: `formatContractAsPromptContext` truncates output field > 2000 chars and appends `[truncated]`\n112\t  - [x] Test: `formatContractAsPromptContext` does NOT truncate output field <= 2000 chars\n113\t  - [x] Test: `buildPromptWithContractContext` returns basePrompt unchanged when contract is `null`\n114\t  - [x] Test: `buildPromptWithContractContext` appends formatted context with separator when contract is provided\n115\t  - [x] Test: round-trip — build prompt with contract, verify all key fields appear in the result\n116\t\n117\t- [x] Task 6: Verify build and tests (AC: #12)\n118\t  - [x] Run `npm run build` — zero TypeScript errors\n119\t  - [x] Run `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, no regressions\n120\t\n121\t## Dev Notes\n122\t\n123\t### Architecture Compliance\n124\t\n125\tThis story implements Epic 4, Story 4.2 (mapped to sprint Epic 13, Story 13-2) \"Output Contract Prompt Injection\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers:\n126\t- **FR18:** System can load a previous task's output contract and inject it as context into the next task's prompt\n127\t- **FR19:** System can pass acceptance criteria, changed file lists, and test results across framework boundaries via output contracts\n128\t- **Architecture Decision 3:** \"Injection: Workflow engine reads contract, appends structured summary to next task's prompt as context.\"\n129\t\n130\t### Implementation Strategy\n131\t\n132\tThe injection is **prompt-level**, not driver-level. The contract context is formatted as a structured text block and appended to the `prompt` string in `DispatchOpts`. This makes it framework-agnostic — all three drivers (claude-code, codex, opencode) already consume `DispatchOpts.prompt`.\n133\t\n134\tKey insight: Do NOT use `appendSystemPrompt` for contract injection. That field is only supported by the claude-code driver (via Agent SDK). Instead, modify the `prompt` field directly, which all drivers handle. The `appendSystemPrompt` field continues to be used only for trace ID injection.\n135\t\n136\tThe workflow engine already has a `dispatchTaskWithResult()` function that constructs the prompt and DispatchOpts. The integration point is there — call `buildPromptWithContractContext()` to enrich the prompt before constructing DispatchOpts.\n137\t\n138\t### What Already Exists\n139\t\n140\t- `OutputContract` interface — `src/lib/agents/types.ts` (lines 67-80), all fields defined\n141\t- `writeOutputContract()` / `readOutputContract()` — `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts`, from story 13-1\n142\t- `DispatchOpts.outputContract` — field already exists in `types.ts` (line 94), type `OutputContract | undefined`\n143\t- `DispatchOpts.prompt` — the primary prompt field consumed by all drivers\n144\t- `dispatchTaskWithResult()` — `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` (line 271+), constructs DispatchOpts and dispatches\n145\t- Barrel exports — `src/lib/agents/index.ts` already exports `writeOutputContract` and `readOutputContract`\n146\t\n147\t### What NOT to Do\n148\t\n149\t- Do NOT use `appendSystemPrompt` for contract injection — only claude-code supports it. Use `prompt` field for universal compatibility.\n150\t- Do NOT modify any driver files — injection is prompt-level, not driver-level.\n151\t- Do NOT validate the contract schema at injection time — trust the typed contract from `readOutputContract()`.\n152\t- Do NOT include the entire `output` field untruncated — large outputs bloat the prompt. Truncate to 2000 chars.\n153\t- Do NOT modify `types.ts` — `OutputContract` and `DispatchOpts.outputContract` already exist.\n154\t- Do NOT wire `readOutputContract()` into the engine in this story — that's story 13-3 (Cross-Framework Workflow Execution). This story only adds the formatting and prompt-building functions, plus the engine call site that uses a passed-in contract.\n155\t\n156\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n157\t\n158\tFrom story 13-1 (Output Contract Schema & Serialization):\n159\t- `output-contract.ts` uses sync I/O (`writeFileSync`, `readFileSync`, `renameSync`) — follow the same pattern for consistency.\n160\t- Tests in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/output-contract.test.ts` use `mkdtempSync` for isolated temp dirs.\n161\t- The `contractFilePath()` helper validates safe filenames — no path traversal.\n162\t- The atomic write pattern: write to `.tmp`, then `renameSync` to final path.\n163\t- `assertSafeComponent()` validates taskName/storyId are safe filename components.\n164\t\n165\tFrom story 12-3 (Driver Health Check at Workflow Start):\n166\t- ~4488 tests passing across 167 test files.\n167\t- All driver infrastructure (factory, claude-code, codex, opencode) is complete and tested.\n168\t\n169\t### Testing Patterns\n170\t\n171\tFollow existing patterns in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/output-contract.test.ts`:\n172\t- Tests already exist for `writeOutputContract` and `readOutputContract` — add new describe blocks for the new functions.\n173\t- Create a fixture `OutputContract` object and reuse it across tests.\n174\t- For truncation testing, create a contract with an `output` field > 2000 characters and verify the formatted output contains `[truncated]`.\n175\t- For the `buildPromptWithContractContext` tests, verify that `null` contract returns the base prompt unchanged.\n176\t\n177\t### Project Structure Notes\n178\t\n179\tFiles to CREATE:\n180\t- None (all changes go in existing files)\n181\t\n182\tFiles to MODIFY:\n183\t- `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` — add `formatContractAsPromptContext()` and `buildPromptWithContractContext()`\n184\t- `src/lib/agents/index.ts` — add barrel exports for the two new functions\n185\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — wire `buildPromptWithContractContext()` into `dispatchTaskWithResult()`\n186\t- `src/lib/agents/__tests__/output-contract.test.ts` — add tests for new functions\n187\t\n188\tFiles NOT to modify:\n189\t- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — OutputContract and DispatchOpts already defined\n190\t- Any driver files (`claude-code.ts`, `codex.ts`, `opencode.ts`) — injection is prompt-level\n191\t- `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — output_contract field is separate concern\n192\t\n193\t### References\n194\t\n195\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 4.2: Output Contract Prompt Injection]\n196\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Decision 3: Output Contract Format — Injection]\n197\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md — FR18, FR19]\n198\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — OutputContract, DispatchOpts interfaces]\n199\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts — writeOutputContract, readOutputContract from story 13-1]\n200\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — dispatchTaskWithResult(), lines 271+]\n201\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/index.ts — barrel exports]\n202\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization.md — previous story context]\n203\t\n204\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n205\t## Verification Requirements\n206\t\n207\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/13-2-output-contract-prompt-injection-proof.md)\n208\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n209\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n210\t\n211\t## Documentation Requirements\n212\t\n213\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n214\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/13-2-output-contract-prompt-injection.md\n215\t\n216\t## Testing Requirements\n217\t\n218\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n219\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n220\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n221\t\n222\t## Dev Agent Record\n223\t\n224\t### Agent Model Used\n225\t\n226\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n227\t\n228\t### Debug Log References\n229\t\n230\tN/A\n231\t\n232\t### Completion Notes List\n233\t\n234\t- Implemented `formatContractAsPromptContext()` — formats OutputContract as structured markdown sections (header, changed files, test results, output summary, acceptance criteria)\n235\t- Implemented `buildPromptWithContractContext()` — appends formatted contract context to base prompt with separator, or returns base prompt unchanged when contract is null\n236\t- Wired injection into `dispatchTaskWithResult()` via optional `previousOutputContract` parameter — story 13-3 will supply the actual contract\n237\t- Added 12 new unit tests covering all ACs; total test count 4523, all passing\n238\t- Output truncation at 2000 chars with `[truncated]` marker confirmed via tests\n239\t\n240\t### Code Review Fixes (Adversarial Review)\n241\t\n242\t- **MEDIUM fix:** Exposed `previousOutputContract` parameter on public `dispatchTask()` API so story 13-3 can pass contracts through the public interface (was only on internal `dispatchTaskWithResult()`)\n243\t- **MEDIUM fix:** Added 2001-char boundary test for output truncation edge case\n244\t- **MEDIUM fix:** Added `buildPromptWithContractContext` mock to workflow-engine tests, added 2 integration tests verifying contract injection flows through `dispatchTask()` to the driver\n245\t- Post-review test count: 4526 (168 files), coverage: 96.8%, all files above 80% per-file floor\n246\t\n247\t### File List\n248\t\n249\t- `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` — added `formatContractAsPromptContext()` and `buildPromptWithContractContext()`\n250\t- `src/lib/agents/index.ts` — added barrel exports for new functions\n251\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — imported `buildPromptWithContractContext` and `OutputContract`, added `previousOutputContract` parameter to both `dispatchTask()` and `dispatchTaskWithResult()`, wired prompt injection\n252\t- `src/lib/agents/__tests__/output-contract.test.ts` — added 13 tests for new functions (12 original + 1 boundary)\n253\t- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — added mock for `buildPromptWithContractContext`, added 2 integration tests for contract injection via `dispatchTask()`\n254\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011PZRovTmoggoFw8vkjbbhy","session_id":"8f19e005-5742-4a5a-a61f-d8a88dc16bec","uuid":"c7d8407a-16b9-42f9-8f31-1a11ce9929c9","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:38:29.382Z"}
